commit d264166d27f34c13f3b043876e3d1bb0b3b6cf50 which made WRT_SMACK_ENABLED

Onward.

Patch Set 4:

(1 comment)

Added one inline comment. Not in modified code, but it looks suspicious

Patch Set 4:

I've created a separate fix for this issue: https://review.tizen.org/gerrit/#/c/20960/

Patch Set 4: Verified+1

Verified by installing other packages of cynara-bootstrap topic branch and installing sample widget requiring a few privileges.
I also wrote a simple application that called cynara_check to see if given permissions are given to the User on installation. It works as expected - permissions declared in manifest are added.
As for the smack labels:
/opt/usr/apps/<pkgid> is given floor label.
/opt/usr/apps/<pkgid>/shared and its subdirectories are given floor label
Other files and directories are given User label which I believe is correct because currently private directories map to User label. I believe this will change in the future when private directories will be given app-specific label.
The only thing that I find wrong is the label of /opt/usr/apps/<pkgid>/shared/trusted which is floor, but it should be something that is writable by other apps (User?). I've submitted a separate patch for this one

/opt/usr/apps/ODBQpKvkS1/shared/data access="_"
/opt/usr/apps/ODBQpKvkS1/shared/trusted access="User" transmute="TRUE"

This still does not fix all the build errors, even for mobile.

Is there a reason the other build fixes were not included?  Perhaps your not building against the actual Tizen 3.0 mobile repositories?

You should see gbs fail to build against mobile because of:
* missing wrt-commons-widget-interface-dao pkgconfig entry in the CMakeList.txt
* spec refs to wrt-preinstall-widgets.service that does not exist
* spec incorrectly listing the libwgt.so in /usr/etc/package-manager/backendlib/libwgt.so when Tizen 3.0 now installs this in /etc/package-manager/backendlib/libwgt.so

I'll make a new patch with you mentioned.

subject: Turn off smack and remove bogus requires for osp-installer
commitMessage:
Turn off smack and remove bogus requires for osp-installer

The smack label creation code is still working on 2.1 assumptions
about the domain layout so disable label creation until the security
team has instituted a domain design for 3.0, and also remove a bogus
arbitrary runtime requirement for osp-installer
